  <name>eio</name>
  <channel>pecl.php.net</channel>
  <summary>Wraps functions of the libeio C library</summary>
  <description>
  This extension wraps functions of the libeio C library written by Marc Lehmann
  &lt;libeio at schmorp dot de&gt;(see http://software.schmorp.de/pkg/libeio.html).
  
  Libeio is a an asynchronous I/O library for C. Features basically include
  asynchronous versions of POSIX API(read, write, open, close, stat, unlink,
  fdatasync, mknod, readdir etc.); sendfile (native on Solaris, Linux, HP-UX,
  FreeBSD); readahead. libeio itself emulates the functions, if they are not
  available on specific(UNIX-like) platform.
  
  Currently Linux platforms supported only.
  </description>
